Script to load the Regional Earth System Data Lab¶

There are four options to load the Regional ESDL (RegESDL) at the JupyterHub (www.https://www.earthsystemdatalab.net/index.php/interact/data-lab/).¶

  • High and low spatial resolution: Cubes can have different spatial resolution (high 0.0083deg or low 0.083deg). Lower resolution facilitates code development and test. Higher resolution is recommended for final analysis. The lower resolution RegESDL is a resampled of the higher one.
  • Temporal and spatial analysis: Depening on how data is stored temporal or spatial analysis speed can be improved. We offer both setting, so it is an users choise.

Estupinan-Suarez, Lina M. 2020.03.04

Load packages¶

In [1]:
using ESDL
In [2]:
using ESDLPlots

Unable to load WebIO. Please make sure WebIO works for your Jupyter client. For troubleshooting, please see the WebIO/IJulia documentation.

Load cubes¶

In [3]:
## This is a high resolution RegESDL for temporal analysis. Observe the "0.0083deg" in the zar file name
chigh = Cube("/home/jovyan/work/datacube/ESDCv2.0.0/esdc-8d-0.0083deg-184x60x60-2.0.0_colombia.zarr/")


## This is a low resolution RegESDL for spatial analysis. Observe the "0.083deg" in the zar file name. 
clow = Cube("/home/jovyan/work/datacube/ESDCv2.0.0/esdc-8d-0.083deg-1x336x276-2.0.0_colombia.zarr/")

Select variable¶

In [4]:
gpp = chigh[variable="GPP"]
evi = clow[variable="EVIterra"]
